flowchart TD
    START([User prompt or manual graph edit])
    START --> FRONTEND[Frontend workflow UI<br/>Autonomous wizard, canvas, properties panel]
    FRONTEND --> GENERATE[POST /api/generate-workflow<br/>Prompt, mode, answers, partial workflow]

    GENERATE --> INTENT[Intent and capability planning<br/>Trigger, actions, data flow, constraints]
    INTENT --> REGISTRY_LOAD[Registry-backed node selection<br/>Canonical node types and operations]
    REGISTRY_LOAD --> GRAPH_BUILD[Graph construction<br/>Nodes, edges, branches, layout]
    GRAPH_BUILD --> GRAPH_VALIDATE[Graph validation<br/>DAG, ports, required trigger, node contracts]
    GRAPH_VALIDATE --> FIELD_OWNERSHIP[Field ownership and manifest<br/>manual_static, buildtime_ai_once, runtime_ai, credential, system]

    FIELD_OWNERSHIP --> ASK_USER[Credential and input discovery<br/>Questions for missing manual and credential fields]
    ASK_USER --> USER_CONFIG[User provides safe configuration<br/>Credentials, resource IDs, static values]
    USER_CONFIG --> SAVE[Save workflow graph<br/>AWS RDB/RDS persistence]

    SAVE --> RUN[Run request<br/>Manual, schedule, webhook, form, chat trigger]
    RUN --> LOAD[Load workflow and execution context<br/>AWS RDB/RDS + user/session context]
    LOAD --> ORDER[Topological execution order<br/>Branch-aware graph traversal]

    ORDER --> NODE_LOOP[For each executable node]
    NODE_LOOP --> TEMPLATE[Template resolution<br/>Use upstream outputs and explicit expressions]
    TEMPLATE --> RUNTIME_ENGINE[Universal Runtime AI Value Engine<br/>Multi-field generation, deterministic repair, validation, audit]
    RUNTIME_ENGINE --> BLOCK{Required runtime fields valid?}
    BLOCK -->|No| FAIL_FAST[Block before provider call<br/>Clear diagnostics and audit trail]
    BLOCK -->|Yes| EXECUTE[Execute node adapter<br/>Google, Gmail, HTTP, DB, logic, AI, utility]
    EXECUTE --> STORE[Store output, status, timing<br/>Cache, checkpoint, AWS RDB/RDS, WebSocket]
    STORE --> MORE{More nodes?}
    MORE -->|Yes| NODE_LOOP
    MORE -->|No| COMPLETE([Workflow execution complete])
